cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper is about a new dataset for machine comprehension in the medical domain, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper applies several baselines and state-of-the-art neural readers to the dataset, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also analyzes the skills required for successful answering, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
